legacy.description: Sharing glimpses of China's splendor.
legacy.name: 环球网

result.text:
Journalists from 13 countries effortlessly made online payments with a single click using e-CNY during their visit to Chengdu's famous "trunk economic zone" - Sanse Road. 

The journalists enjoyed Sichuan Opera performances, savored local delicacies, participated in interactive games, all while using e-CNY payment. Ali Abbas, Senior Investigative Reporter at https://t.co/JdedW6OEng in Pakistan, was particularly amazed by the convenience of e-CNY payment. "It is very convenient. With it, you can pay for everything," he said.

E-CNY, the first digital currency issued by a major economy, is a central bank digital currency issued in China. After undergoing public testing in 2021, it is now being implemented in 17 provinces as pilot areas. China's leadership in online payment development has greatly improved residents' lives, making everything more convenient.

The Sanse Road Block is a vibrant spot along the Jinjiang Lohas Greenway in Chengdu, China. Completed by CCCC-Tianjin Dredging CO., Ltd. in 2021, the greenway has become a bustling "trunk economic zone" where locals flock to the flea market and unwind.
#TravelogueofChina

result.text: Journalists from 13 countries explored the Zhanqi Village in @Chengdu_China. This charming village is intersected by the Jinjiang Greenway constucted by CCCC-Tianjin Dredging Co., Ltd. Visitors can immerse themselves in the serene atmosphere and admire the breathtaking scenery. The village also boasts a museum showcasing intangible cultural heritage such as the production of Doubanjiang (fermented bean paste). Teddy Trilaksono from Indonesia praised the museum, saying, "The museum here is really good, so I can understand the village and know the stories of culture." #TravelogueofChina
